{"captured_at": "2026-07-13T11:39:47.951919Z", "created_at": "Fri Feb 28 10:03:58 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-02-28T10:03:58Z", "created_at_ts": 1582884238, "display_name": "Analilia Mejia", "handle": "analilia_mejia", "id": "1233332002767634432", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 262, \"reply_count\": 18, \"like_count\": 1328, \"quote_count\": 24, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "Wow... @glennbeck - way to (intentionally) get the story WRONG.\nWhen my mother was pregnant with me, my father fell at his factory job and BROKE HIS BACK. They were so poor (no insurance, no savings, nothing) my mother had to send my 1 yr old sister to live with my grandmother", "tweet_type": "tweet", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "Analilia_Mejia"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-13T11:39:47.951919Z", "created_at": "Fri Feb 28 10:03:58 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-02-28T10:03:58Z", "created_at_ts": 1582884238, "display_name": "Analilia Mejia", "handle": "analilia_mejia", "id": "1233332004588019714", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 48, \"reply_count\": 1, \"like_count\": 380, \"quote_count\": 1, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "When I was born, my mother had to send me away to my grandmother - BECAUSE SHE COULDNT AFFORD TO KEEP HER CHILDREN, despite working two jobs and cleaning houses. 40 years after getting us “back” my mother still recounts the pain poverty inflicted on her. As a mother, I understand", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "Analilia_Mejia"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-13T11:39:47.951919Z", "created_at": "Fri Feb 28 10:03:58 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-02-28T10:03:58Z", "created_at_ts": 1582884238, "display_name": "Analilia Mejia", "handle": "analilia_mejia", "id": "1233332005527523328", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 41, \"reply_count\": 2, \"like_count\": 318, \"quote_count\": 0, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "In American, @glennbeck, both then &amp;now, poverty tears people apart. Mothers lose children, children lose futures, families break. My story of being “sent to live on the side of a mountain”(in a earthquake prone country) is about how poor people are forced to make awful choices", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "Analilia_Mejia"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-13T11:39:47.951919Z", "created_at": "Fri Feb 28 10:03:59 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-02-28T10:03:59Z", "created_at_ts": 1582884239, "display_name": "Analilia Mejia", "handle": "analilia_mejia", "id": "1233332006513250304", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 50, \"reply_count\": 7, \"like_count\": 333, \"quote_count\": 0, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "Poverty almost destroyed my family. My mother still tears up about having to let got of her daughters because she couldn’t work &amp;care for my sick father. @glennbeck could have read the @TheAtlantic article or spoken to @mollyesque. Instead he misrepresents my truth.", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "Analilia_Mejia"}
